ss=title> Planar progression </span><hr size=1> When dealing with Planar flags, always go through ALL quest texts. Don't use shortcuts -- if you miss even one minor flag, you won't be able to progress through the Planes. You can always backpeddle, but figuring out what you're missing can prove tedious. When in doubt, speak with Seer Mal Nae`Shi in the Plane of Knowledge. <br>
<br>
Note: The Tier 2 planes have been opened up, providing you're of appropriate level to zone in. If you want to progress further through PoP (Sol Ro Tower, elemental planes, Fire and Time), you will need to complete ALL pre-flags. <br>
<br>
Plane of Knowledge <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
No entry requirement, level one. <br>
<br>
Plane of Tranquility <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
Level 46. <br>
<br>
Plane of Disease <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
Level 46. <br>
<br>
Plane of Innovation <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
Level 46. <br>
<br>
ONCE INSIDE: <br>
To open the Factory Door, you must kill Xanamech Nezmirthafen. Do this under the guidance of Nitram Anizok. <br>
<br>
Plane of Justice <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
Level 46. <br>
<br>
ONCE INSIDE: <br>
To reach The Seventh Hammer, you must complete the six trials and loot the Marks off the final boss of each. Say to The Tribunal, &quot;I seek knowledge,&quot; and use the Mark of Justice on a portal to go into The Seventh Hammer's room. (NOTE: The Seventh Hammer is not actually required for any Planar Progression.) <br>
<br>
Plane of Nightmare <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
Level 46. <br>
<br>
Lair of Terris Thule <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
-Chat with Adroha Jezith and the sickened Elder Poxbourne in the Plane of Tranquility. <br>
-Complete the maze event in the Plane of Nightmare, killing the Construct of Nightmares. <br>
-Hail Elder Poxbourne. <br>
<br>
Plane of Valor <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
-Chat with Mavuin, he wants to plead his case before the Tribunal. <br>
-Complete any of the six trials in the Plane of Justice. <br>
-Ask The Tribunal &quot;What evidence of Mavuin?&quot; <br>
-Hail Mavuin again in the basement. (Note: Also grants access to the Plane of Storms.) <br>
<br>
ONCE INSIDE: <br>
To open the door to Aerin`Dar's lair, you must gather the hearts of a Larvae, Crawler and Razorfiend for Paralin Notion. Go through ALL quest text. Then, you'll need three pieces of the crystalline globe (dropped from undead vassals, luminii crawlers and frogs). Give these pieces to Captain Ryglot Cupperhide. <br>
<br>
Plane of Storms <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
-Chat with Mavuin, he wants to plead his case before the Tribunal. <br>
-Complete any of the six trials in the Plane of Justice. <br>
-Ask The Tribunal &quot;What evidence of Mavuin?&quot; <br>
-Hail Mavuin again in the basement. (Note: Also grants access to the Plane of Valor.) <br>
<br>
Drunder, Fortress of Zek [Plane of Tactics] <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
-Chat with Giwin Mirakon and slay the Manaetic Behemoth. Hail Giwin after its death. <br>
<br>
Halls of Honor <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
Kill Aerin`Dar in the Plane of Valor and hail the Planar Projection which spawns after her death. You must enter the Halls of Honor through the entrance from Valor, below Aerin`Dar's lair. <br>
<br>
Temple of Marr <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
Complete the three trials in the Halls of Honor: The slaying of Rydda`Dar, the Villager Trial and the Crazed Norrathian Trial. <br>
<br>
Bastion of Thunder <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
Obtain a Storm Giant Head, Sash, Bone and Beard from lesser giants in the Plane of Storms. You'll also need two different Medallions from named giants. Talk to Askr the Lost. You'll need to do some hand-ins and combines. Upon doing these and going through quest text, you'll be flagged for the Bastion of Thunder. <br>
<br>
ONCE INSIDE: <br>
-To gain access to the upper towers: Combine the four different gems (Tornado, Lightning, Blizzard, Sandstorm) from the four wings (dropped by lower level giants) in a Ring of Torden, dropped by 1st floor bosses. <br>
-To gain access to Agnarr's area: Combine the four different spheres (Tornado, Lightning, Blizzard, Sandstorm) from the four wings (dropped by upper level giants) in an Unadorned Symbol of Torden, dropped by 2nd floor bosses. <br>
<br>
Ruins of Lxanvom [Crypt of Decay] <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
-Talk to Alder Fursteil (&quot;What ward?&quot;). <br>
-Kill Grummus in the castle of the Plane of Disease. <br>
-Hail Alder Fursteil in Tranquility. <br>
<br>
ONCE INSIDE: <br>
To gain access to Bertoxxulous: Kill Carprin Deatharn, Bishop Toluwon, Vindor Mawnil, Raex Pwodill and High Priest Ultor Szanvon (one spawns after the other). Hail Tarkil Adan after the High Priest's death. <br>
<br>
Plane of Torment <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
-Kill Terris Thule in the Plane of Nightmare. <br>
-Kill Bertoxxulous in the Crypt of Decay, hail Elder Fuirstel afterward. <br>
-Tell Fahlia Shadyglade &quot;I will go to Torment.&quot; <br>
<br>
ONCE INSIDE: <br>
-To gain access to Saryrn: Kill an Unimaginable Horror in the stomach of Baraguj Szuul and loot the container. In this container, combine the Orbs of Anguish, Agony, Pain and Suffering (dropped off the Avatars by the same names). <br>
<br>
Tower of Solusek Ro <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
-Kill Saryrn in the Plane of Torment, hail the Planar Projection (you ALSO need the Keeper of the Sorrows in Torment). <br>
-Kill the Zek brothers, Vallon and Tallon. Hail the Projection after each of their deaths. <br>
-Kill Lord Mithaniel Marr, hail the Projection. <br>
-Ask Grand Librarian Maelin, &quot;What information?&quot; <br>
<br>
ONCE INSIDE: <br>
-To gain access to Solusek Ro: Kill the five mini-bosses, Rizlona, Xuzl, Arlyxir, The Protector of Dresolik and Jiva. <br>
<br>
Doomfire, the Burning Lands [Plane of Fire] <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
-Kill Solusek Ro in the Tower of Sol Ro. <br>
<br>
Reef of Coirnav [Plane of Water] <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
-Kill Rallos Zek in the Plane of Tactics. <br>
-Kill Agnarr the Storm Lord in the Bastion of Thunder. Flag from Karana <br>
-Talk to Grand Librarian Maelin in Knowledge (&quot;What information?&quot;) (Note: Also grants access to Air and Earth.) <br>
<br>
Eryslai, the Kingdom of Wind [Plane of Air] <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
-Kill Rallos Zek in the Plane of Tactics. <br>
-Kill Agnarr the Storm Lord in the Bastion of Thunder. Flag from Karana. <br>
-Talk to Grand Librarian Maelin in Knowledge (&quot;What information?&quot;) (Note: Also grants access to Earth and Water). <br>
<br>
Vegarlson, the Earthen Badlands [Plane of Earth] <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
-Kill Rallos Zek in the Plane of Tactics. <br>
-Kill Agnarr the Storm Lord in the Bastion of Thunder. Flag from Karana. <br>
-Talk to Grand Librarian Maelin in Knowledge (&quot;What information?&quot;) (Note: Also grants access to Air and Water). <br>
<br>
Ragrax, Stronghold of the Twelve [Plane of Earth B] <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
-Complete the ring events in Plane of Earth A, and kill the Mystical Arbitor of Earth. <br>
<br>
Plane of Time [A] <br>
REQUIREMENTS: <br>
-Obtain the following items, received after hailing the Essence that spawns following the death of the corresponding god. Combine them in an Odylic Vial and then speak with Chronographer Muon in the Plane of Innovation: <br>
Sphere of Coalesced Water (Plane of Water, Coirnav the Avatar of Water) <br>
<br>
Globe of Dancing Flame (Plane of Fire, Fennin Ro the Tyrant of Fire) <br>
<br>
Mound of Living Stone (Plane of Earth, Avatar of Earth) <br>
<br>
Amorphous Cloud of Air (Plane of Air, Xegony the Queen of Air).<br>
<br>
<br>
